What you need to know:

Matsuyama won the 85th Masters on Sunday, becoming the first Japanese man to win a major title and capping a 25-year dream that started when his father began teaching him the sport when he was only four years oldWith his victory at Augusta National, Matsuyama now has six career US PGA triumphs, matching the total achieved by all other Japanese players on the US tourIn his first trip to Augusta National, Matsuyama won the Silver Cup as low amateur and shared 27th